    "body": "[BundlePhobia](https://bundlephobia.com/result?p=@eth-optimism/contracts@0.2.9) shows that our dependencies for `@eth-optimism/contracts` are only about ~4mb. A majority of this is `ganache-core`, which we're only using because of our current state dump process. Once we move to ChugSplash we should be able to cut `ganache-core` out entirely.\r\n\r\nRunning `du -sh *` highlights the real cause of the package size:\r\n```sh\r\nk@kpc:~/Projects/work/optimism/optimism/packages/contracts$ du -sh *\r\n35M\tartifacts\r\n28M\tartifacts-ovm\r\n24K\tbin\r\n136K\tcache\r\n136K\tcache-ovm\r\n8.0K\tCHANGELOG.md\r\n4.0K\tcodechecks.yml\r\n800K\tcontracts\r\n76K\tdeploy\r\n11M\tdeployments\r\n3.9M\tdist\r\n4.0K\thardhat.config.ts\r\n4.0K\tLICENSE.txt\r\n1.8M\tnode_modules\r\n4.0K\tpackage.json\r\n4.0K\tREADME.md\r\n20K\tscripts\r\n52K\tsrc\r\n8.0K\ttasks\r\n976K\ttest\r\n4.0K\ttsconfig.build.json\r\n184K\ttsconfig.build.tsbuildinfo\r\n4.0K\ttsconfig.json\r\n4.0K\ttslint.json\r\n```\r\n\r\n`artifacts` and `artifacts-ovm` are huge! But why? On a whim I deleted the `build-info` folders inside of each `artifacts` and `artifacts-ovm`, here's what I get now:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n2.3M\tartifacts\r\n2.2M\tartifacts-ovm\r\n24K\tbin\r\n136K\tcache\r\n136K\tcache-ovm\r\n8.0K\tCHANGELOG.md\r\n4.0K\tcodechecks.yml\r\n800K\tcontracts\r\n76K\tdeploy\r\n11M\tdeployments\r\n3.9M\tdist\r\n4.0K\thardhat.config.ts\r\n4.0K\tLICENSE.txt\r\n1.8M\tnode_modules\r\n4.0K\tpackage.json\r\n4.0K\tREADME.md\r\n20K\tscripts\r\n52K\tsrc\r\n8.0K\ttasks\r\n976K\ttest\r\n4.0K\ttsconfig.build.json\r\n184K\ttsconfig.build.tsbuildinfo\r\n4.0K\ttsconfig.json\r\n4.0K\ttslint.json\r\n```\r\n\r\nHuge difference. So let's make sure to drop the build-info folders in the published versions of our contracts. I'll also work on getting something in place that checks the build sizes before publish and warns about large folders.",
